                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>The Dutch celebrate the feast of St Nicholas by giving presents to family members and friends on 5 December, the eve of the saint’s name day (6 December).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p>Their sister <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_407">Willemien</rs> was also not going to be there at Christmas.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="a" xml:id="note-t-a">
                            

<p>Here meaning ‘Bijzonder, opmerkelijk’ (special).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="3" xml:id="note-t-3">
                            

<p>Theo’s co-workers at Goupil’s; <ref target="let019.xml#n-11">see letter 19, n. 11.</ref></p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
